Chiromo Hospital Group will on Saturday host the second edition of MindFest to encourage individuals living with mental illness. The event is aimed at showing that it is possible to be functional and be the best version of yourself, living a full and purposeful life. Since the onset of the COVID-19 pandemic there has been a rise in poor mental health cases amid the pandemic that caused a total disruption of livelihoods. The public and private sectors have come together actively to promote mental health. In celebration of the world mental health day this year, Chiromo Hospital Group has partnered with Safaricom, Kenya ni Mimi, Ms. World Kenya among other partners for the second edition of MindFest. The event will create a space to showcase gifts and talents and emphasize more that there is so
much more to an individual than their diagnosis. Also Read: The Theme of the event is Arts; hence the event will have performances within the creative spectrum of poetry, spoken word, sketch, paint, photography, Music and dance. This is also aligned to the hospitals global campaign #TUFUNGUKE, it’s time to open up and gear up towards a society free from mental health stigma and discrimination. The festival  focuses on people with a Mental illness lived experience, highlighting that there is so much more to a person than their illness and in no way is it an inability. Video Of The Day: Former sports CS Hassan Wario convicted over Rio games scam